      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates QoI change <2% between medium and fine mesh; GCI < 5%.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study (coarse 0.8 mm, medium 0.4 mm, fine 0.2 mm global element size) was performed. QoI change between medium and fine meshes was 0.9% for stiffness and 1.4% for yield force. Grid Convergence Index (GCI) was 2.1% and 3.3% respectively. The production mesh (0.4 mm global, 0.15 mm at interface) was selected as the converged discretization."
    },
    {
